Hi, I am using Moose for my phase field fracture modelling. There are variables "ux uy" and order parameter "v"
I used StressDivergenceTensors for Residual R_u and Jacobian J_uu. and PhaseFieldFractureMechanicsOffDiag for J_uv
AllenCahn, ACInterface, TimeDerivative for R_v and J_vv (I guess).
At this time, everything went well.
And then I built my own class for J_vu. When I added this action, the program could not be converged.
Do you have any clues? Does the phase field module has its own way to deal with J_vu?
Below is my class code for J_vu
xxx::ScalarFieldVarCoupleStressOffDiag(
    const InputParameters & parameters)
  : DerivativeMaterialInterface<Kernel>(parameters),
    _base_name(isParamValid("base_name") ? getParam<std::string>("base_name") + "_" : ""),
    _ndisp(coupledComponents("displacements")),
    _disp_vars(coupledIndices("displacements")),
    _dF_dc_dstrain(getMaterialProperty<RankTwoTensor>(derivativePropertyNameFirst(_base_name + "stress", _var.name())))
{
}

Real
xxx::computeQpOffDiagJacobian(unsigned int jvar)
{
  if (_ndisp != _mesh.dimension())
    paramError(
        "displacements",
        "The number of variables supplied in 'displacements' must match the mesh dimension.");
  for(unsigned int n=0; n<_ndisp; n++)
  {
    if (jvar == _disp_vars[n])
    {
      Real val = 0.0;
      for (unsigned int k = 0; k < Moose::dim; ++k)
        val += 0.5 * (_dF_dc_dstrain[_qp](n,k) + _dF_dc_dstrain[_qp](k,n)) * _grad_phi[_j][_qp](k);
      return val * _test[_i][_qp];
    }
  }

  // Returns if coupled variable is not ux or uy
  return 0.0;
